{
  "genre": "classical",
  "mode": "energize",
  "mixStrategy": "This Classical energize arrangement in D major is built around a driving, rhythmic energy that builds across 6 segments (~7.5s each). FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Cello, 20-300Hz, MIDI 38-50) anchors the harmonic foundation with strong root notes and Alberti-style movement. Chords (String Ensemble, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 50-69) provide sustained harmonic body with close voicings that change precisely with the progression. Melody (Acoustic Piano, 1-8kHz, MIDI 62-81) delivers a lyrical, singable theme with antecedent-consequent phrasing, chord tones on strong beats. Texture (Flute, 3kHz+, MIDI 74-88) adds shimmering counter-melody ornaments in the highest register. HARMONIC PLAN: Segments 1-2 (0-15s): I\u2192IV\u2192V\u2192I progression establishing the key. Segments 3-4 (15-30s): I\u2192vi\u2192IV\u2192V progression adding emotional depth and building intensity. Segments 5-6 (30-45s): Return to I\u2192IV\u2192V\u2192I with climactic energy, then settling. ENERGY ARC: 0.4\u21920.6\u21920.8\u21920.9\u21921.0\u21920.7. Velocity and note density increase through seg 5, then ease in seg 6. RHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Cello bass locks with strong beats, piano melody breathes between phrases, strings sustain through changes, flute ornaments fill gaps in melody. All tracks change chords on the same beats for total cohesion. Quarter note = 0.522s. Each chord lasts ~2 beats (1.044s) or 4 beats (2.088s) depending on harmonic rhythm.",
